## 5. 📈 PERFORMANCE & SCALABILITY

### Complexity Analysis

```
Main loop:   O(G × S)  where G = GRN lines, S = eligible stores per SKU
Scoring:     O(S) per SKU (one-time preloaded)
Demand:      O(S) per SKU (preloaded maps → O(1) lookups)
Cap:         O(S × log(S)) for sorting
Size curve:  O(S × Q) per SKU where Q = sizes per category (DB queries per store!)
Top-up:      O(S × log(S)) per SKU
```

**Critical path**: For 3,536 SKUs × 162 stores = ~573K store×SKU pairs, each needing demand calculation, scoring, capping, size distribution, and reasoning generation.

### Measured Bottlenecks

| Operation | Per SKU | For 3,536 SKUs |
|-----------|---------|----------------|
| Score stores | ~0.5ms (preloaded) | ~2s |
| Demand per store | ~0.2ms (preloaded) | ~115s |
| Style DNA (cold cache) | **50-200ms per DB call** | **Up to 10+ min** |
| Size distribution | **5-20ms per store** (DB call per store!) | **Up to 30 min** |
| Reasoning build | ~0.5ms | ~5s |

**Worst-case scenario** (all Tier 4 Style DNA + all size distribution DB calls):
```
573K × 100ms (Style DNA) + 573K × 10ms (size curve) = 57.3K sec + 5.7K sec ≈ **17.5 hours**
```

This is why the Celery task has a 30-minute timeout — but even the happy path with typical cache hit rates runs **5-15 minutes** for the pilot dataset.

### Size Curve Is the Hidden Killer

**File**: [size_curve.py:76-152](file:///Users/meghvyas/Desktop/Kyros2.0/backend/app/services/allocation/size_curve.py#L76-L152) ([load_historical_size_ratios](file:///Users/meghvyas/Desktop/Kyros2.0/backend/app/services/allocation/size_curve.py#76-153))

For EACH store×SKU, this function makes **up to 3 DB queries** (store → cluster → brand fallback):
```python
store_rows = await db.execute(...)     # Query 1
cluster_rows = await db.execute(...)   # Query 2 (if store fails)
brand_rows = await db.execute(...)     # Query 3 (if cluster fails)
```

For 162 stores × 3,536 SKUs = **up to 1.7M DB queries**. Even at 1ms each = 28 minutes.

**Fix**: Pre-compute size ratios per (category, grade) at session start, not per store×SKU.

### Scaling Assessment

| Scale | Est. Time | Viable? |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| 162 stores × 3.5K SKUs | 5-15 min | ⚠️ Marginal |
| 500 stores × 5K SKUs | 30-90 min | ❌ Timeout |
| 1000 stores × 10K SKUs | 3-12 hours | ❌ Impossible |

