### Missing Guardrails (Must Add Before Pilot)

#### 1. Max Store Allocation Cap
```python
# engine.py — after final_allocations computed
MAX_STORE_PCT = 0.25  # No single store should get > 25% of available
for store_id, qty in final_allocations.items():
    if qty > available_units * MAX_STORE_PCT:
        logger.warning("Store %s getting %.0f%% of inventory", store_id, qty/available_units*100)
        final_allocations[store_id] = int(available_units * MAX_STORE_PCT)
```

#### 2. Skew Detection
```python
# After allocation: check Gini coefficient of distribution
def gini_coefficient(allocations: dict[UUID, int]) -> float:
    values = sorted(allocations.values())
    n = len(values)
    if n == 0: return 0
    cumsum = sum((i+1) * v for i, v in enumerate(values))
    return (2 * cumsum) / (n * sum(values)) - (n + 1) / n

gini = gini_coefficient(final_allocations)
if gini > 0.6:  # highly skewed
    session.warnings.append(f"SKU {sku.sku_code}: allocation is highly skewed (Gini={gini:.2f})")
```

#### 3. Anomaly Flags per Allocation Line
```python
# Add to ai_reasoning JSONB
"risk_flags": {
    "stockout_risk": weeks_cover < 2,
    "over_allocation_risk": final_qty > 3 * weekly_ros * season_weeks_remaining,
    "low_confidence": ai_confidence == "LOW",
    "no_history": ros_source == "minimum_presentation",
    "heavy_cap_applied": cap_scale_factor < 0.3,
}
```

