## 9. 🏗️ PRODUCTION READINESS

### 🔴 Critical Blockers (MUST FIX Before Pilot)

| # | Issue | Impact | Fix Effort |
|---|-------|--------|------------|
| 1 | **Synthetic week spreading** masks real demand patterns | All allocations are based on artificial ROS | 2 days: Require [week_start_date](file:///Users/meghvyas/Desktop/Kyros2.0/backend/app/services/ingestion/processor.py#846-862) OR accept flat ROS with explicit warning |
| 2 | **Full DELETE on sales re-upload** | Data loss on partial failure | 1 day: Use idempotent upsert, not delete+insert |
| 3 | **Mid-loop `db.commit()`** | Inconsistent state on crash | 0.5 day: Single transaction with flush (not commit) |
| 4 | **No concurrent run protection** | Race condition on duplicate requests | 0.5 day: `SELECT FOR UPDATE` on session |
| 5 | **Un-normalized scoring** | ROS dominates, grades/cover meaningless | 1 day: Normalize to [0,1] before weighting |

### 🟡 Will Destroy User Trust (Fix in Week 1)

| # | Issue | Impact |
|---|-------|--------|
| 6 | No warning when most stores default to grade C | User sees low allocations, doesn't understand why |
| 7 | No utilization summary ("450 of 500 units unallocated") | VP asks "where's my inventory?" |
| 8 | `was_overridden` flag is wrong (compares to raw, not final) | Review analytics are meaningless |
| 9 | CSV export loads all lines into memory | 500K+ lines → OOM for production-sized datasets |
| 10 | No summary email/notification when allocation completes | User has to keep polling the UI |

### 🟢 Acceptable Imperfections (Can Ship With)

| Issue | Why It's OK For Pilot |
|-------|----------------------|
| Style DNA matching is premature | Tier 1-3 cover pilot adequately |
| Cannibalization factor is fixed | Manual override covers edge cases |
| No inter-store transfers | Pre-season only in pilot |
| Single Celery worker | Pilot has 1 brand, 1 concurrent run |
| boto3 unused | No impact, just unnecessary dep |

